[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Adds passive life and energy regeneration at a rate you control. The keeper slowly recovers over time without needing to sleep, eat, or meditate.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Life Regeneration Rate[/b] — how much life is restored per tick. Default 2. Set to 0 to disable life regen specifically while keeping energy regen on.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Energy Regeneration Rate[/b] — how much energy is restored per tick. Default 1. Set to 0 to disable energy regen while keeping life regen on.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Regeneration Delay[/b] — how many seconds between ticks. Default 5.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Show Regeneration Updates[/b] — optional floating text above the keeper's head (similar to the energy-spend text vanilla shows). Off if you'd rather keep the HUD clean.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Main menu update notice[/b] — flags when a newer version of this mod (or other mods in my collection) is on Nexus. Click to open its Nexus page. Opt-out via "Check for Updates".[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/42]Exhaust-less[/url] — halves (or eliminates) the cost of energy, gratitude, and sanity. Pairs perfectly with passive regen for a truly unbothered playthrough.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/65]FasterCraft Reloaded[/url] — speed up crafting. More crafts per regen tick.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/53]Longer Days[/url] — stretches the day cycle. More daylight, more regen before you need to sleep.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

